  <h2>Video Summary</h2>
  <p>This full tutorial demonstrates a complete carburettor and intake manifold replacement on a 150cc scooter fitted with a GY6 157QMJ engine — one of the most common engine platforms in Chinese-built scooters including the BTC Riva, Santini Capri, and many others. The procedure is filmed on a VIP-style bodywork scooter, but the engine access and component layout are directly applicable to any GY6-engined machine.</p>

  <h2>What the Video Covers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Removing the body panel and access cover to reach the carburettor</li>
    <li>Disconnecting the fuel line, throttle cable, and choke linkage safely</li>
    <li>Removing the intake manifold (inlet pipe) between the engine head and carburettor</li>
    <li>Inspecting the old carburettor for wear, blockage, and gasket condition</li>
    <li>Installing a new PD24J or equivalent carburettor on the replacement intake manifold</li>
    <li>Reconnecting all cables and lines with correct routing</li>
    <li>Initial idle adjustment and cold-start testing</li>
  </ul>

