  <h2>Parts &amp; Tools Referenced</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Replacement carburettor: PD24J (standard for GY6 150cc / 157QMJ) — available from <a href="https://www.vmcchineseparts.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">VMC Chinese Parts</a>, <a href="https://www.scooterworks.com/collections/gy6" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Scooterworks USA</a></li>
    <li>Intake manifold: GY6 150cc inlet manifold with carb-to-head gasket</li>
    <li>JIS cross-head screwdrivers (#1, #2)</li>
    <li>Needle-nose pliers (for fuel line clamps)</li>
    <li>Flat-blade screwdriver (for carb clamps and jets)</li>
    <li>New fuel line clamps (recommended if reusing old hoses)</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="tip">
    💡 <strong>Applicable models:</strong> This procedure is relevant to any GY6 157QMJ-engined scooter, including the BTC Riva 50/125, Santini Capri 50/125, La Souris Sourini, Sym Orbit II, Kymco Agility 125, and any other scooter sharing the 150cc GY6 platform.
